{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The event of the Austrian Anschluss was, for me, very easily understandable, as I understood German fluently and perfectly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So starting from the speeches of Hitler and even the newspaper of the which was the Nazi official journal, and Zeitung.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I could read because, first of all, we learned in school the Gothic print and writing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So probably due to that, my knowledge of the press comments and general announcements, and so on, in German was no difficult, not-- I didn't have to translate it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I could understand it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- shortly after the Anschluss-- obviously, my father and the family was very concerned for my uncle, the doctor, who wasn't married, even, to get him out of Austria.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it's interesting how, with a Hungarian passport, a Jew, my father-- you will probably take a photo of the very few pictures I've got left-- did not particularly have the appearance of a Jew-- could travel up into Austria from Hungary with a Hungarian passport and be let in without any problem.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Probably not even fearing his own safety, went and collected my uncle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Probably he took him some papers along already and brought him back to Sapron, where he stayed a while with our family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, he used to come and see us on weekends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He had a, a car and used to come down from Austria just to have a Sunday meal or for a Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that way, he brought him out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And no doubt, my father hasn't told me all the details.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was too young to understand it, what he saw and what was going on.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
